<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99902474597223></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99902474597223><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=99902474597223>RE: Help</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=99902474597223#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2568><span id= >philoscope</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>63 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Aug 28th 2:52 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.83]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you're a wood elf (not Hum / 1/2-elf) you can do the CB belt quest.&nbsp;&nbsp;I believe that the quest out of the Kelethin warriors' guild also sometimes gives armour.  Otherwise, you'll probably start making enough money soon to start buying armour yourself.  failing disaster, you should be fully clothed in leather or better well before level 10.<br>&nbsp;<br>Looking for love.....pity there's so little in humanity.</td></tr>
