<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100012651491529></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100012651491529><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=100012651491529>RE: Help</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=100012651491529#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=79214><span id=Scholar>Ravensveil</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>242 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Sep 10th 8:55 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.13]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You want to be level 4 before you start taking on orcs cents in gfay. If you turn in belts, you get xp, faction, and tattered armor or the occasional shield. Not bad. Ofcourse, it is all small, so if you are human or half-elf like me, the armor is useless.<br>The belts are a good way to level, but you will level WAY past your skills with this, so it is really up to you.<br><br>Fastest way to make money: In Gfay. Kill bats. As many as&nbsp;&nbsp;you can. When you get a stack or two of bat wings, auction them. You can sell a stack of 20 for about 2 or 3 plat easily to a druid. You can also collect and sell stacks of bone chips. Again, you will probably find druids and clerics who will buy because of Felwith quest. also, the occassional necro who will need it to cast pets. I see alot of gnome necros around on qeull.<br><br>At lvl 4 or 5 you can start taking on cents. Especially if you team up with a mage or other caster. <br><br>While you can complete the belt quest, there is a nother option for earning money. The belts will each sell for between 5gp and 2pl EACH. You can easily make 10pl selling a backpack full of them.  If you are a half or woodelf, buy your leather from the merchant off the newbie lift. Aluweane. She is off to the left of newbie lift. She will have sizes you need. <br><br>with 4plat, I bought shirt and sleeves. Pants are next. Buy them a component at a time until you get them all. Might as well. It will help you as you go.<br><br>Also, watch for what people are auctioning to buy. Alot of times they will be things you can aquire and get xp as you do. Batwings, bone chips. Orc hatchets. Sometimes silks and pixie dust. Silks will sell very well because of the infrequency of drops. That is true in any zone, really, but the price you get varies place to place. Don't be afraid to travel to sell what you collect. And don't be afraid to buy items in one zone to sell in a farther zone. it's called playing merchant,and players will gladly pay for convenience.<br><br>Peace<br><br>&nbsp;<br>"In waking a tiger, use a very long stick." -Mao Tse-Tung. Did he go to Stonebrunt too?</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
